From Mark Eckenwiler Subject Re Once tapped your code is no good any In sez Do the police normally reveal every tap they do even if no charges are laid In many ways it would be a positive step if they had Judges set time limits on warrants I Under the relevant federal law USC d the authorizing judge must notify the targets within days after the tap period with extensions This is the normal Of course no wiretap law would be complete without the Unless Clause which in subsection d reads like this On an ex parte showing by the gov't without opposition since that would obviously involve notice to the targets of good cause to a judge of competent jurisdiction the serving of the inventory required by this subsection the order itself dates of interception may be postponed emphasis added Followups directed to a few select MORAL Always Choose the Right Sort of Parents Before You Start in to be Rough George Ade Mark Eckenwiler panix eck